One of the most fun groups I ever had was four clerics, a necro and a monk.  It started out with a pally tanking and two clerics with a necro slowing at the undead camp in PoV.  As people logged and I did /who all guild the only people online were clerics so by the end we had the monk pulling and four clerics bashing/nuking/stunning/dotting/healing and having a great time.  I've never done six - I think we would have had a really hard time tanking without the necro to slow at that camp at least - but five clerics and a necro could be a blast.   <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane<BR>
